##HOW TO DO CLIPPING CAMPAIGN ( ON WHOP )
To find clipping campaigns, one of the most common platforms is Whop. You can start by simply searching for Whop on Google and creating an account using your Gmail ID. After logging in, navigate to the Content Rewards section, where you will find various available campaigns and communities. From there, you can explore and join the campaigns or servers that match your interest.

COMMON PROBLEMS AND SOLUTION 

Campaign or server not available in your region - 
Sometimes, you may notice that certain campaigns or servers are not accessible in your region. This usually happens because the campaign owner has restricted access for specific countries. In such cases, you can use a VPN to bypass this limitation. Turn on the VPN, access Whop through the website (this method does not work properly on the app), and then join the desired campaign or server.
Once you have successfully joined, you can turn off the VPN without any issues. Most of the time, these restrictions are just default settings, and campaign owners do not actively monitor them. As long as you follow the campaign rules and instructions properly, you can continue working without problems.

Scam server on whop - 
Not all servers on Whop are trustworthy, so it is important to verify before joining any campaign. A good starting point is to check the rating of the server—anything below 4.5 stars should be avoided. You should also be cautious of campaigns related to course selling or “quick money” business models, as these are often less reliable.
Another effective method is to interact with the community. Talk to members in the server and observe how active and responsive the environment is. Before starting any work, it is highly recommended to contact the support team by opening a ticket and asking how to begin. If you receive a clear and timely response, it indicates that the server has a reliable support system. Lack of response is usually a red flag and should be taken seriously.

Botting accusations - 
Botting is strictly prohibited in almost all clipping campaigns, and engaging in it will lead to a ban. However, there are situations where your content performs very well and gains views rapidly, which might be mistakenly flagged as botting by the system.
If this happens, you should immediately contact the support team and explain your situation clearly. In most cases, legitimate growth can be verified, and the issue gets resolved. Staying transparent and following campaign rules is the best way to avoid such problems.

